author: whitlock
msg: AXISCPP-463 When the server throws a fault (not a user-defined fault in the wsdl), throw back an exception to the client application with the correct information in it. This fix adds in OtherFaultException which encapsulates other soap faults generated by the server. OtherFaultException extends SoapFaultException and is thrown back to the client application.
